<h1><mark>Jaipur – The Pink City of India</mark></h1>

<p><b>Jaipur</b> is the capital city of Rajasthan. It is popularly known as the <i>Pink City</i> of India. Jaipur is famous for its <mark>history, culture, forts, and palaces</mark>.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Why Jaipur is Called the Pink City</h2>
<p>In the year <b>1876</b>, Jaipur was painted pink to welcome the Prince of Wales. Pink color represents <i>hospitality</i>. Since then, Jaipur is known as the <u>Pink City</u>.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Famous Tourist Places in Jaipur</h2>

<p><b>1. Amer Fort</b><br>
Amer Fort is one of the most popular tourist attractions in Jaipur. It shows the <i>royal lifestyle</i> of Rajput kings. The fort is built on a hill and looks very beautiful.</p>

<p><b>2. Hawa Mahal</b><br>
Hawa Mahal is also called the <mark>Palace of Winds</mark>. It has many small windows. These windows allow cool air to pass inside the palace.</p>

<p><b>3. City Palace</b><br>
City Palace is located in the heart of Jaipur. It is a mixture of <i>Rajasthani</i> and <i>Mughal</i> architecture.</p>

<p><b>4. Jantar Mantar</b><br>
Jantar Mantar is an astronomical observatory. It was built to study <b>time</b> and <b>space</b>. It is a <mark>UNESCO World Heritage Site</mark>.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Culture and Traditions of Jaipur</h2>
<p>Jaipur is famous for traditional dresses, folk music, and dance. People wear colorful clothes. The culture of Jaipur reflects <u>Indian heritage</u>.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Food of Jaipur</h2>
<p>Jaipur is known for its delicious food. Some famous dishes are <b>Dal Baati Churma</b> and <b>Ghewar</b>. Tourists love Rajasthani food.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Historical Importance</h2>
<p>Jaipur was founded by <b>Maharaja Sawai Jai Singh II</b>. The city has strong historical roots. Old traditions are still followed today.</p>

<p><i>"Jaipur is not just a city, it is a beautiful journey into India's royal past."</i></p>

<hr>

<h2>Interesting Facts</h2>
<p>Jaipur was one of the first planned cities of India. The city follows traditional architecture rules. The old city buildings are still painted pink.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Mathematical & Scientific Touch</h2>
<p>Jantar Mantar helps calculate time using the sun. It works on basic principles like <b>Earth rotation</b>. Time calculation is related to 24 hours and 60 minutes.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Tourism Then and Now</h2>
<p>Earlier tourism was <del>limited</del>. Now tourism is <mark>highly developed</mark>. Old systems are <del>discarded</del> and new facilities are added.</p>

<hr>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>Jaipur is a perfect blend of history and modern life. It attracts tourists from all over the world. Jaipur truly represents the <b>pride of India</b>.</p>

